            "error": null,
            "answer_markdown": "## ESVS-grounded answer\n\nThe ESVS 2024 Clinical Practice Guidelines on the Management of Abdominal Aorto-Iliac Artery Aneurysms do not cover the management or assessment pathway for patients presenting with an infrarenal abdominal aortic mural thrombus with distal embolisation, unless the thrombus is inside a stent graft after prior endovascular aneurysm repair. No direct ESVS pathway applies to de novo non-aneurysmal aortic mural thrombus with embolic sequelae.\n\n## Interpretation\n\nNon-ESVS interpretation (clinical reasoning beyond the retrieved guideline text):\nIn the absence of ESVS guidance specific to de novo infrarenal aortic mural thrombus with distal embolisation, assessment and management should be guided by expert consensus, individual patient factors, and local protocols. Pathways relevant to aneurysm or post-repair thrombus do not apply unless underlying aneurysm or stent graft is present. Multidisciplinary input is often warranted for this rare entity.",
